abstract: Senate steps up pace in moving legislation forward, as if to compensate for months of inaction; Democrats and Republicans cooperate on adding amendments to bill providing money for several federal departments but fail to muster enough votes to take up jobs legislation championed by Pres Obama as way to help revive the economy.
snippet: Cooperation on money bills contrasted with continued gridlock over jobs legislation.
lead_paragraph: Cooperation on money bills contrasted with continued gridlock over jobs legislation.

headline.main: Senate, at Least for a Day, Gets Back to Legislating
headline.print_headline: Senate, at Least for a Day, Gets Back to Legislating
